  {
    "title": "An unholy cabal has taken over the East West Media group and at the core of it i...",
    "description": "An unholy cabal has taken over the East West Media group and at the core of it is Gias Uddin Rimon. Rimon used to be a reporter for a Bangla newspapers and later joined the police service as an ASP. In 2008, he fled to the UK. There, he claims to have finished law school and became a barrister; he also claims to be a lecturer on police education in two low-tier British universities. Sometime after the 5th of August 2024, he returned to Bangladesh to become the deputy managing director of East West Media Group, the media wing of Bashundhara Group \u2014 leveraging his closeness to Tarique Rahman. Misusing the Premier's name \u2014 he has taken hold of the transfer and promotion \u2018business\u2019 in the police service (this is a story for another day). Now, Rimon has turned the media outlets of East West Group into a propaganda vehicle (I'm not sure whether he's doing it in a self styled way or whether the top leadership of Bangladesh Nationalist Party-BNP approved any such tasteless move). Examples can be found in Kaler Kantho\u2019s front page on 26th February. When most people were outraged over the way Ahsan H Mansur was unceremoniously removed as the Bangladesh Bank governor, Kaler Kantho ran a report justifying this indefensible incident by manufacturing facts against him. And today's audacious statement terming the Yunus government 'illegitimate'. From now onwards, whatever you come across on Kaler Kantho and rest of the lineup \u2014 take it with a whole bucket of salt.",
    "link": "https://www.facebook.com/saerzulkarnain/posts/pfbid0jzT3oTu3PuvB6PvPMHN3jd7Q8S6yiPNfTc8EPBrZSV4uoQ8uHTZeJeEBM3seYPcil",
    "guid": "https://www.facebook.com/saerzulkarnain/posts/pfbid0jzT3oTu3PuvB6PvPMHN3jd7Q8S6yiPNfTc8EPBrZSV4uoQ8uHTZeJeEBM3seYPcil",
    "pubDate": "2026-03-07T00:23:07.046339+00:00",
    "image": null
  },
